        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>The Society of the United Hebrew Charities&#44;<lb/>
                325 NORTH FIFTH STREET&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia&#44; September 24&#91;&#44;&#93; 1884<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev.S. Morais<lb/>
                Respected Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>The Board of Government<lb/> earnestly solicits your influence and urgent appeal to the<lb/> members of your congregation&#44; in order that the necessary<lb/> means may be obtained to continue as heretofore to prop&#45;<lb/>erly assist our ever increasing poor. The great influx of<lb/> emigrants and poor people from New Jersey&#44; New York and<lb/> other localities have very largely increased the number<lb/> of our recipients&#44; who have to be cared for by this society.<lb/> Our funds having become exhausted&#44; we were obliged to <lb/> draw on our Treasurer who kindly advanced the requisite<lb/> sums to aid our people&#44; consequently we are now largely<lb/> in debt to our Treasurer. Extra exertions will have to be made<lb/> by our ever ready and benevolent community to carry us through this<lb/> fall and winter. In hope that your efforts may be success&#45;<lb/>ful as usual I remain.<lb/></p>
            <p>Very respectfully yours<lb/>
                M. Lazarus<lb/>
                Asst. Secty<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
